title: Vicky Donor
overview: A man is brought in by an infertility doctor to supply him with his sperm, where he becomes the biggest sperm donor for his clinic.

title: Lage Raho Munna Bhai
overview: Munna Bhai embarks on a journey with Mahatma Gandhi in order to fight against a corrupt property dealer.

title: City Lights
overview: With the aid of a wealthy erratic tippler, a dewy-eyed tramp who has fallen in love with a sightless flower girl accumulates money to be able to help her medically.

title: Rang De Basanti
overview: The story of six young Indians who assist an English woman to film a documentary on the freedom fighters from their past, and the events that lead them to relive the long-forgotten saga of freedom.

title: Dom za vesanje
overview: In this luminous tale set in the area around Sarajevo and in Italy, Perhan, an engaging young Romany (gypsy) with telekinetic powers, is seduced by the quick-cash world of petty crime, which threatens to destroy him and those he loves.

title: Moonrise Kingdom
overview: A pair of young lovers flee their New England town, which causes a local search party to fan out to find them.

title: Marriage Story
overview: Noah Baumbach's incisive and compassionate look at a marriage breaking up and a family staying together.

title: Roman Holiday
overview: A bored and sheltered princess escapes her guardians and falls in love with an American newsman in Rome.

title: Good Bye Lenin!
overview: In 1990, to protect his fragile mother from a fatal shock after a long coma, a young man must keep her from learning that her beloved nation of East Germany as she knew it has disappeared.

title: Silver Linings Playbook
overview: After a stint in a mental institution, former teacher Pat Solitano moves back in with his parents and tries to reconcile with his ex-wife. Things get more challenging when Pat meets Tiffany, a mysterious girl with problems of her own.

title: Annie Hall
overview: Neurotic New York comedian Alvy Singer falls in love with the ditzy Annie Hall.

title: My Cousin Vinny
overview: Two New Yorkers accused of murder in rural Alabama while on their way back to college call in the help of one of their cousins, a loudmouth lawyer with no trial experience.

title: Do lok tin si
overview: This Hong Kong-set crime drama follows the lives of a hitman, hoping to get out of the business, and his elusive female partner.

title: Kind Hearts and Coronets
overview: A distant poor relative of the Duke D'Ascoyne plots to inherit the title by murdering the eight other heirs who stand ahead of him in the line of succession.

title: The Circus
overview: The Tramp finds work and the girl of his dreams at a circus.

title: The Big Lebowski
overview: Jeff "The Dude" Lebowski, mistaken for a millionaire of the same name, seeks restitution for his ruined rug and enlists his bowling buddies to help get it.

title: It Happened One Night
overview: A renegade reporter and a crazy young heiress meet on a bus heading for New York, and end up stuck with each other when the bus leaves them behind at one of the stops.

title: His Girl Friday
overview: A newspaper editor uses every trick in the book to keep his ace reporter ex-wife from remarrying.

title: Three Billboards Outside Ebbing, Missouri
overview: A mother personally challenges the local authorities to solve her daughter's murder when they fail to catch the culprit.

title: The Purple Rose of Cairo
overview: In New Jersey in 1935, a movie character walks off the screen and into the real world.
